---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending in -TY — Abstract Nouns That Score"
  description="Scrabble words ending in -TY with full scoring. ANXIETY 14pts, PUBERTY 14pts, NOVELTY 13pts. Master the -TY suffix for abstract nouns that deliver consistent points."
  keywords="scrabble words ending in ty, anxiety scrabble points, novelty scrabble, puberty scrabble word, ty suffix words scrabble, abstract nouns scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -TY — Abstract Nouns That Score","description":"Scrabble words ending in -TY with full scoring. ANXIETY 14pts, PUBERTY 14pts, NOVELTY 13pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ty"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is ANXIETY worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ANXIETY scores 14 points (A=1, N=1, X=8, I=1, E=1, T=1, Y=4). The X tile contributes 8 of those 14 points, and as a 7-letter word it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is NOVELTY a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! NOVELTY scores 13 points (N=1, O=1, V=4, E=1, L=1, T=1, Y=4) and is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. The V and Y tiles provide most of the scoring power in this 7-letter bingo candidate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What -TY words are good for bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The best -TY bingo words include ANXIETY (14pts+50 bonus), PUBERTY (14pts+50), POVERTY (15pts+50), NOVELTY (13pts+50), and LIBERTY (12pts+50). All use common tiles with one or two premium letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -TY — Abstract Nouns That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words ending in -TY form some of the most common abstract nouns in English — and many are exactly 7 letters long, making them bingo candidates. The T+Y ending only costs 5 points (T=1, Y=4), but the words built around it often contain X, V, W, or other premium tiles that push scores into double digits.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POVERTY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ANXIETY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PUBERTY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NOVELTY</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring -TY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">POVERTY — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, O=1, V=4, E=1, R=1, T=1, Y=4 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">POVERTY uses V (4pts), P (3pts), and Y (4pts) for 15 points from common tiles. Add the 50-point bingo bonus for 65 total. Every letter appears multiple times in the tile bag, making this a highly achievable bingo.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">😰 ANXIETY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · A=1, N=1, X=8, I=1, E=1, T=1, Y=4 · X tile power</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📚 PUBERTY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · P=3, U=1, B=3, E=1, R=1, T=1, Y=4 · P + B combo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎁 NOVELTY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · N=1, O=1, V=4, E=1, L=1, T=1, Y=4 · V drives score</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🗽 LIBERTY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · L=1, I=1, B=3, E=1, R=1, T=1, Y=4 · Reliable bingo</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More -TY Words Worth Learning</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOUNTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DEPUTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEISTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NICETY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THIRSTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WITTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for -TY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-TY is a bingo factory:</span> ANXIETY, POVERTY, NOVELTY, PUBERTY, LIBERTY — all exactly 7 letters. Keep T+Y on your rack and look for 5 connecting letters for the 50-point bonus.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ANXIETY uses X naturally:</span> X is worth 8 points but hard to play. ANXIETY places it mid-word between vowels (A-N-X-I-E-T-Y), solving the usual problem of needing it next to a vowel on the board.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Shorter -TY for defence:</span> WITTY (11pts), GUSTY (9pts), DUSTY (9pts), and PETTY (10pts) are 5-letter words that block premium squares while delivering solid scores.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The -TY suffix excels at <span class="text-white font-medium">turning premium consonants into bingos</span>. X (ANXIETY), V (POVERTY, NOVELTY), B (PUBERTY), and W (THIRSTY) all find natural homes in -TY words.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid -TY word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-tion/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -TION</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ize/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -IZE</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ny/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -NY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ly/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -LY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ment/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -MENT</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
